Commonly used tools to monitor SSL/TLS certificate expiry include dedicated services like TrackSSL, UptimeRobot, and StatusCake, along with infrastructure monitoring solutions such as Datadog, Site24x7, and ManageEngine. These tools automate tracking, alerting administrators before certificates expire to prevent downtime. 
